731
00:53:05,259 --> 00:53:07,932
I never expected Cole to get this close.

732
00:53:08,819 --> 00:53:11,970
I thought you kept better track
of your ex-employees.

733
00:53:13,459 --> 00:53:16,212
No way to anticipate
he'd become this involved.

734
00:53:16,779 --> 00:53:19,373
Who is he? Obviously not just a cop.

735
00:53:20,499 --> 00:53:23,730
He was a brilliant soldier.
West Point, that kind of thing.

736
00:53:24,459 --> 00:53:28,532
I found him in Vietnam.
Recruited him for a special projects unit.

737
00:53:29,779 --> 00:53:31,656
The Program, we called it.

738
00:53:31,819 --> 00:53:34,333
He handled a lot of odd jobs for us.

739
00:53:35,059 --> 00:53:36,970
-Such as?
-Now, Mr. Deverell...

740
00:53:37,259 --> 00:53:39,898
...don't ask about things
you don't really want to know.

741
00:53:39,979 --> 00:53:42,698
Suffice to say, to the people he hunted
for us...

742
00:53:42,779 --> 00:53:45,339
...he was known as "The Glimmer Man."

743
00:53:46,539 --> 00:53:48,575
There'd be nothing but jungle...

744
00:53:49,459 --> 00:53:50,972
...then a glimmer...

745
00:53:52,859 --> 00:53:54,417
...then you'd be dead.

746
00:53:55,019 --> 00:53:57,169
Why isn't he still with you?

747
00:53:57,419 --> 00:54:01,094
He was booted out of the program in '84.
Went native on us.

748
00:54:02,939 --> 00:54:04,770
Made up his own assignments.

749
00:54:04,939 --> 00:54:06,850
Disappeared...for months.

750
00:54:07,219 --> 00:54:09,130
Ended up in Thailand...

751
00:54:09,979 --> 00:54:12,413
...chanting in some temple or other.

752
00:54:13,139 --> 00:54:15,653
They say he was saved by a holy man.

753
00:54:17,099 --> 00:54:21,138
So many stories about this fella,
I don't know which ones are true anymore.

754
00:54:26,979 --> 00:54:29,095
-What do we do about him?
-Broom him.

755
00:54:29,899 --> 00:54:32,697
Time to lose everybody
who knows anythin'.

756
00:54:34,819 --> 00:54:36,616
And I mean everybody.

757
00:54:38,459 --> 00:54:39,892
Johnny's no threat.

758
00:54:41,179 --> 00:54:44,489
I beg to differ. He's already spilled
to the shrink.

759
00:54:46,179 --> 00:54:49,057
The poor boy knows too much.
Simple as that.

760
00:54:50,419 --> 00:54:51,977
Johnny'll do what I say.

761
00:54:52,059 --> 00:54:54,209
Let me put this another way.

762
00:54:54,619 --> 00:54:57,292
I have four loose links in this operation:

763
00:54:57,579 --> 00:54:59,649
Two cops, you, and the boy.

764
00:55:00,659 --> 00:55:02,297
Three of you have to go.

765
00:55:02,539 --> 00:55:04,291
You can choose which three.

766
00:55:07,379 --> 00:55:09,529
You'll have to do it yourself.

767
00:55:10,059 --> 00:55:11,538
Frank, I'll take care of Johnny.

768
00:55:11,619 --> 00:55:14,087
Who's gonna take care of Cole
and Campbell?

769
00:55:14,259 --> 00:55:16,489
I'll put Donald on the others right away.

770
00:55:16,579 --> 00:55:18,092
That's the spirit.

771
00:55:18,259 --> 00:55:20,727
Now, come on in. The water's fine.

772
00:57:39,459 --> 00:57:40,414
Shit!

773
00:58:28,659 --> 00:58:30,570
Take the kids upstairs.

774
00:58:36,899 --> 00:58:38,491
-John Cole?
-Yes.

775
00:58:38,739 --> 00:58:41,014
Miller and Russo from lnternal Affairs.

776
00:58:41,099 --> 00:58:43,169
We have a warrant for your arrest.

777
00:58:43,579 --> 00:58:46,218
Do you want to take a minute
to gather a few things?

778
00:58:46,299 --> 00:58:49,018
No, that's perfectly all right.
I'm ready to go.

779
00:59:38,579 --> 00:59:40,729
Coldest winter I can remember in LA.

780
00:59:41,499 --> 00:59:42,898
Wettest, too.

781
01:01:39,499 --> 01:01:41,012
They got you, too.

782
01:01:41,099 --> 01:01:43,613
No, I bought all this shit after the riots.

783
01:01:43,779 --> 01:01:46,134
It means we're close, man, we're close.

784
01:01:46,299 --> 01:01:48,017
Do I look like I give a shit?

785
01:01:48,099 --> 01:01:52,138
You better give a shit, 'cause they ain't
gonna stop till they get us both.

786
01:01:56,379 --> 01:01:58,210
Does this say, "deer antler"?

787
01:01:59,259 --> 01:02:00,692
Give me that.

788
01:02:01,739 --> 01:02:04,936
-It was a free sample.
-There's a whole case over here.

789
01:02:05,019 --> 01:02:06,930
Just stay out of my shit.

790
01:02:07,419 --> 01:02:10,968
Can I just take this moment to tell you
how moved I am deeply?

791
01:02:11,139 --> 01:02:13,209
Yeah, well, that makes one of us.

792
01:02:13,979 --> 01:02:16,493
I found somethin'
on your ex-wife's phone records.

793
01:02:16,579 --> 01:02:18,809
Someone called the house the night
she was killed.

794
01:02:18,899 --> 01:02:23,051
They called six times, only talked about 1 0
or 1 5 seconds each time.

795
01:02:23,619 --> 01:02:25,530
You got a number or somethin'?

796
01:02:26,259 --> 01:02:29,888
Could I take those CDs?
They look like I could still use them.

797
01:02:30,819 --> 01:02:32,218
Got it. Come on.

798
01:02:32,379 --> 01:02:35,337
Could I ask you somethin'?
Did you actually live in this shitbox?

799
01:02:35,419 --> 01:02:36,977
Man, will you come on?

800
01:02:57,019 --> 01:02:59,374
Now, what if this is really our guy?

801
01:02:59,539 --> 01:03:01,450
-We'll reason with him.
-Right.

802
01:03:05,179 --> 01:03:06,373
-What?
-Police!

803
01:03:09,259 --> 01:03:10,817
I'm Detective Cole,
this is Detective Campbell...

804
01:03:10,899 --> 01:03:13,367
...with the Los Angeles Police Department.

805
01:03:13,459 --> 01:03:15,689
We'd like to ask you some questions
about some calls...

806
01:03:15,779 --> 01:03:18,088
...you may have made to a Dr. Dunleavy.

807
01:03:21,499 --> 01:03:23,888
You look like you just came from a riot.

808
01:03:24,139 --> 01:03:24,889
Thanks.

809
01:03:24,979 --> 01:03:27,334
He looks like he just came from a riot.

810
01:03:27,739 --> 01:03:31,129
Yeah, this number's billed to me,
but it's my daughter's phone.

811
01:03:34,659 --> 01:03:36,411
I know you, don't l?

812
01:03:37,379 --> 01:03:40,530
Yeah, you know me. You put my boyfriend
through a window.

813
01:03:42,419 --> 01:03:45,013
High school, window. I remember now.

814
01:03:45,619 --> 01:03:48,133
You're Johnny Deverell's girlfriend,
aren't you?

815
01:03:48,219 --> 01:03:48,935
So?

816
01:03:49,019 --> 01:03:52,932
So, I was just wondering, how long
have you known Dr. Dunleavy?

817
01:03:54,179 --> 01:03:56,215
I don't know any Dunleavy.

818
01:03:56,939 --> 01:03:59,612
You called him the night he was killed.

819
01:04:00,299 --> 01:04:03,052
Yeah. Well, it wasn't me.
I don't need a shrink.

820
01:04:03,979 --> 01:04:05,890
We never said he was a shrink.

821
01:04:08,939 --> 01:04:11,612
Okay, I knew him but I didn't call him.

822
01:04:12,459 --> 01:04:13,812
I wonder who did?

823
01:04:15,299 --> 01:04:16,414
Johnny did.

824
01:04:16,979 --> 01:04:19,857
When he got busted with the coke,
they made him see a shrink.

825
01:04:19,939 --> 01:04:21,895
The shrink was Dunleavy, right?

826
01:04:22,219 --> 01:04:23,174
Millie.

827
01:04:23,579 --> 01:04:26,889
Let me tell you something, sweetheart,
the games are over.

828
01:04:27,059 --> 01:04:29,414
I want you to tell me right now...

829
01:04:29,819 --> 01:04:32,731
...why Johnny was making phone calls
from this room.

830
01:04:33,139 --> 01:04:34,891
He was afraid to call from home.

831
01:04:34,979 --> 01:04:35,968
Why?

832
01:04:36,139 --> 01:04:39,654
His stepfather. Johnny knew
some bad things he was doing.

833
01:04:39,979 --> 01:04:42,857
Would you happen to know
where we could find this boy?

834
01:04:42,939 --> 01:04:46,136
His stepfather put him away
at Our Lady Of Angels.

835
01:04:47,739 --> 01:04:51,049
You don't think Deverell would kill
his own stepson, do you?

836
01:04:52,539 --> 01:04:55,337
Right. Dumb question.
Let's get out of here.

837
01:05:50,579 --> 01:05:53,093
-You all right, Johnny?
-Yeah, never been better.

838
01:05:53,179 --> 01:05:55,818
Yeah, we need to ask some questions
about your stepdad.

839
01:05:55,899 --> 01:05:57,218
He's a prick.

840
01:05:58,139 --> 01:05:59,731
Yeah, besides that.

841
01:06:01,139 --> 01:06:03,016
Did your dad kill Dunleavy?

842
01:06:04,259 --> 01:06:07,296
Yeah, I tried to call him,
I tried to warn him, I swear to God.

843
01:06:07,379 --> 01:06:09,449
We know, we know. It's all right.

844
01:06:10,859 --> 01:06:13,293
All right, everybody just relax. Police.

845
01:06:13,619 --> 01:06:14,847
Why'd he do it?

846
01:06:15,019 --> 01:06:17,852
Okay, he had Donald kill his translator...

847
01:06:19,179 --> 01:06:23,457
...because she knew that my father was
smugglin' in some bad shit from Russia.

848
01:06:24,299 --> 01:06:26,130
And I found out about it.

849
01:06:26,419 --> 01:06:29,775
So, he got all freaked out,
and thought I told Dr. Dunleavy.

850
01:06:30,259 --> 01:06:32,853
So he had Donald kill him and his wife...

851
01:06:32,939 --> 01:06:35,328
...and made it look
like the serial killer did it.

852
01:06:35,419 --> 01:06:36,772
Who was helpin' him?

853
01:06:36,859 --> 01:06:38,372
Some little guy.

854
01:06:39,699 --> 01:06:41,132
Southern accent....

855
01:06:42,259 --> 01:06:44,136
-Smith.
-Yeah, the government guy.

856
01:06:44,219 --> 01:06:45,618
Who's Smith?

857
01:06:45,979 --> 01:06:47,935
You're about to find out.

858
01:06:48,019 --> 01:06:50,010
Sister, take this boy
and keep an eye on him.

859
01:06:50,099 --> 01:06:52,294
Don't let anything happen to him.
Don't leave him alone.

860
01:06:52,379 --> 01:06:55,337
Yes, of course.
I'll take care of you, Johnny. Come.

861
01:07:01,979 --> 01:07:03,412
See you later, Joe.

862
01:07:27,499 --> 01:07:28,693
How you doin'?

863
01:07:30,859 --> 01:07:33,009
Jack, what a pleasant surprise--

864
01:07:37,859 --> 01:07:40,532
You know, in most states in this country...

865
01:07:40,739 --> 01:07:44,254
...kidnapping is still a no-no.
Hell, we don't even do it anymore.

866
01:07:44,339 --> 01:07:46,728
Do me a favor. Spare me the drama and...

867
01:07:46,899 --> 01:07:49,493
...tell me a story.
What's Deverell smuggling?

868
01:07:50,419 --> 01:07:52,296
I have no idea what you're talking about.

869
01:07:52,379 --> 01:07:53,289
Really?

870
01:07:55,379 --> 01:07:57,768
Goddamn, Jack! What are you doin', man?

871
01:07:58,779 --> 01:08:02,931
Deverell's killed four people to hide
something, and I want to find out what.

872
01:08:03,179 --> 01:08:05,135
You're a fuckin' psycho.

873
01:08:06,219 --> 01:08:08,528
I don't know what the hell
he's talkin' about.

874
01:08:08,619 --> 01:08:09,847
Well, you're a cop!

875
01:08:09,939 --> 01:08:11,497
Aren't you gonna help?

876
01:08:12,139 --> 01:08:13,254
Okay.

877
01:08:13,779 --> 01:08:15,815
But I'm a really bad shot.

878
01:08:15,979 --> 01:08:18,447
-Stay out of it.
-I'm just tryin' to help.

879
01:08:19,259 --> 01:08:21,375
Kill me if you like, you son of a bitch.

880
01:08:21,459 --> 01:08:24,098
I still have no idea
what you're talkin' about.

881
01:08:25,579 --> 01:08:28,616
Jack, I know we've had some harsh words
in the past....

882
01:08:36,979 --> 01:08:39,493
-I tell you I do not know--
-Okay....

883
01:08:45,259 --> 01:08:47,727
I need that hand. Jack, I need that hand.

884
01:08:48,139 --> 01:08:50,528
You know I will. Right about....

885
01:08:50,899 --> 01:08:53,094
All right! Time! Game over!

886
01:09:07,179 --> 01:09:08,976
God I miss you, Jack.

887
01:09:10,779 --> 01:09:13,930
So many young men today
just won't go that extra mile.

888
01:09:14,939 --> 01:09:17,692
I miss you too, Smith. Now, what is it?

889
01:09:18,459 --> 01:09:19,892
Deverell is smugglin'...

890
01:09:19,979 --> 01:09:21,731
...chemical weapons in from Russia.

891
01:09:21,819 --> 01:09:25,971
I made the contacts for him. The deal's
being brokered by the Russian Mafia.

892
01:09:27,379 --> 01:09:30,530
Would one of you gentlemen mind
callin' me an ambulance?

893
01:09:30,699 --> 01:09:32,769
So, what's he doin' with this stuff?

894
01:09:32,859 --> 01:09:36,169
Deal's bein' done tomorrow.
Some welfare hotel downtown.

895
01:09:36,499 --> 01:09:39,218
He's sellin' it to a bunch
of Serbian freedom fighters.

896
01:09:39,299 --> 01:09:40,778
You mean terrorists.

897
01:09:41,099 --> 01:09:43,249
Semantics. You say tomato--

898
01:09:43,859 --> 01:09:46,817
No, motherfucker, I didn't say, "tomato."
I said, "terrorists."

899
01:09:46,899 --> 01:09:48,048
You work for the government.

900
01:09:48,139 --> 01:09:50,653
Why would you, of all people,
help Deverell?

901
01:09:52,979 --> 01:09:55,777
To get rich, son. To get rich, why else?

902
01:09:56,339 --> 01:09:57,567
You got that?

903
01:09:58,219 --> 01:09:59,857
Yeah, I got that.

904
01:10:02,899 --> 01:10:05,333
Well, aren't you the grown-up spy?

905
01:10:07,499 --> 01:10:09,091
What do you want?

906
01:10:09,459 --> 01:10:13,054
I want you and your friends
to leave me alone. Forget that I exist.

907
01:10:13,139 --> 01:10:14,254
I already have.

908
01:10:14,339 --> 01:10:15,818
Don't make me come back and kill you.

909
01:10:15,899 --> 01:10:17,173
-I won't.
-Good.

910
01:10:23,379 --> 01:10:26,576
Gentlemen, we must not forget
the little matter...

911
01:10:27,699 --> 01:10:30,213
-...of the ambulance.
-I only shot you in one foot.

912
01:10:30,299 --> 01:10:32,096
Hobble to a hospital.

913
01:10:44,059 --> 01:10:48,098
Well, safe to assume, folks,
that the rainiest winter in memory is over.

914
01:10:48,179 --> 01:10:52,457
Sunny and dry weather for tomorrow
and for the entire five-day period.

915
01:10:52,659 --> 01:10:55,969
Everything we could hope for
in this part of the country....

916
01:10:56,939 --> 01:10:59,976
Deverell is smugglin' chemical weapons in
from Russia.

917
01:11:00,659 --> 01:11:03,127
The deal's bein' brokered
by the Russian Mafia.

918
01:11:03,219 --> 01:11:05,289
-Who is this?
-So, how's that, asshole?

919
01:11:05,379 --> 01:11:08,416
I know you're friends with everyone
from the postman to the President...

920
01:11:08,499 --> 01:11:10,854
...but no one will touch you
with a ten-foot pole...

921
01:11:10,939 --> 01:11:12,531
...when this shit gets out. Understand?

922
01:11:12,619 --> 01:11:14,132
Detective Cole.

923
01:11:14,739 --> 01:11:17,299
You are persistent, I'll give you that.

924
01:11:17,379 --> 01:11:20,291
Looks like I got somethin' you want,
you got somethin' I want.

925
01:11:20,379 --> 01:11:22,529
-What might that be?
-Donald.

926
01:11:22,899 --> 01:11:24,890
Donald's your triggerman, isn't he?

927
01:11:24,979 --> 01:11:25,889
I'm listening.

928
01:11:25,979 --> 01:11:27,731
I want him, not you.

929
01:11:27,819 --> 01:11:30,538
Deliver him to me with a nice bow
and the murder weapon.

930
01:11:30,619 --> 01:11:32,257
I'll take it from there.

931
01:11:32,339 --> 01:11:36,252
You take the tape...my name
gets clean...your name stays clean.

932
01:11:36,819 --> 01:11:38,650
Everybody's happy, how's that?

933
01:11:38,739 --> 01:11:39,854
Done.

934
01:11:40,939 --> 01:11:42,611
Why don't you meet me tomorrow?

935
01:11:42,699 --> 01:11:46,135
I'm doing a little business at a place
called the Ovington Arms, downtown.

936
01:11:46,219 --> 01:11:49,097
Apartment D-14.
Would 1 0:00 be good for you?

937
01:11:55,699 --> 01:11:57,530
Why does this gotta be so complicated?

938
01:11:57,619 --> 01:11:59,655
This isn't complicated.
It's nothing but a game.

939
01:11:59,739 --> 01:12:01,695
Reminds me of an old Persian tactician...

940
01:12:01,779 --> 01:12:04,612
...trying to teach his young troops strategy.

941
01:12:04,859 --> 01:12:06,929
That, later on, came to be known as chess.

942
01:12:07,019 --> 01:12:08,737
So, we're gonna bore 'em to death now?

943
01:12:08,819 --> 01:12:11,777
Young warriors used to like
to fight head-on.

944
01:12:12,139 --> 01:12:14,289
Old warriors like to wait...

945
01:12:14,739 --> 01:12:18,618
...let their opponents expose the board,
work themselves into a corner....

946
01:12:18,699 --> 01:12:21,088
Time to go. Sun Tzu, The Art of War.

947
01:12:21,659 --> 01:12:24,298
Sun Tzu. Just keeps gettin' stranger.

948
01:12:29,339 --> 01:12:30,692
Donald's your triggerman, isn't he?

949
01:12:30,779 --> 01:12:31,655
I'm listening.

950
01:12:31,739 --> 01:12:33,297
I want him, not you.

951
01:12:33,459 --> 01:12:36,212
Deliver him to me with a nice bow
and the murder weapon.

952
01:12:36,299 --> 01:12:37,652
I'll take it from there.

953
01:12:37,739 --> 01:12:40,333
Take the tape...my name gets clean...

954
01:12:40,859 --> 01:12:44,329
...your name stays clean.
Everybody's happy, how's that?

955
01:12:45,099 --> 01:12:45,975
Done.

956
01:12:47,819 --> 01:12:50,811
Guess your ass just got sold
down the river, shithead.

957
01:13:18,939 --> 01:13:21,214
This won't take long. Just a quick pick up.

958
01:13:21,299 --> 01:13:22,698
I'm sure it won't.

959
01:14:27,299 --> 01:14:28,652
Shabby, but chic.

960
01:14:37,859 --> 01:14:39,770
Either we're a little early...

961
01:14:39,859 --> 01:14:41,975
...or our hosts are a little late.

962
01:14:49,379 --> 01:14:51,449
What the hell is going on, Donald?

963
01:14:52,339 --> 01:14:53,488
You tell me.

964
01:14:55,899 --> 01:14:59,972
You think you're gonna hand me over
to Cole. Bad move, fruitcake.

965
01:15:01,259 --> 01:15:03,568
I don't know what you're talking about.

966
01:15:07,339 --> 01:15:08,772
You'll never get out of here.

967
01:15:08,859 --> 01:15:10,850
No, this is my show from now on.

968
01:15:18,379 --> 01:15:20,370
Positively Shakespearean.

969
01:15:21,579 --> 01:15:22,568
"To be...

970
01:15:23,339 --> 01:15:24,055
"...or not to be! "

971
01:15:24,459 --> 01:15:25,335
Time to go.

972
01:15:25,419 --> 01:15:28,172
Wait. We don't know how many guys are
in there.

973
01:15:28,259 --> 01:15:31,410
What do you want me to do?
Wait till they all kill each other?

974
01:15:31,499 --> 01:15:33,296
If the old warriors are patient and...

975
01:15:33,379 --> 01:15:35,574
...all the young warriors,
they kill each other and...

976
01:15:35,659 --> 01:15:37,012
...that's how we get to be old.

977
01:15:37,099 --> 01:15:38,737
I like that plan too. You listened well.

978
01:15:38,819 --> 01:15:40,491
That's what I told you in the bar.

979
01:15:40,579 --> 01:15:42,854
I don't know why I don't listen to myself.
I'm stupid.

980
01:15:42,939 --> 01:15:44,258
Let's just wait.

981
01:15:45,339 --> 01:15:46,977
Drop the guns! Police!

982
01:15:48,499 --> 01:15:49,329
Put your guns down!

983
01:15:49,419 --> 01:15:50,647
Drop that fuckin' gun!

984
01:15:50,739 --> 01:15:51,808
Drop the gun now!

985
01:15:51,899 --> 01:15:53,298
Drop the gun, boy.

986
01:17:18,939 --> 01:17:19,894
Freeze!

987
01:17:23,859 --> 01:17:25,258
Just drop it!

988
01:17:25,459 --> 01:17:26,733
You, too!

989
01:17:27,579 --> 01:17:28,455
Where do you live?

990
01:17:28,539 --> 01:17:31,656
-Around the corner.
-Well, get your ass around the corner!

991
01:17:31,739 --> 01:17:34,173
And take little Whoopi Goldberg with you.

992
01:17:34,939 --> 01:17:36,133
Jesus Christ.

993
01:17:36,619 --> 01:17:38,337
Showdown on Sesame Street.

994
01:17:39,019 --> 01:17:41,772
Big Bird will pop out of one
of these doors next.

995
01:18:31,179 --> 01:18:31,975
Hi!

996
01:18:43,179 --> 01:18:44,214
Out here!

997
01:18:47,019 --> 01:18:49,817
Hurry, man! I can't hold on much longer!

998
01:18:52,299 --> 01:18:54,733
Oh, God, don't look down.
Don't look down.

999
01:18:56,299 --> 01:18:57,698
Oh, don't look up.

1000
01:19:09,099 --> 01:19:10,612
All right, hang on.

1001
01:19:10,779 --> 01:19:12,610
Yeah. That's a good idea, man.

1002
01:19:12,699 --> 01:19:14,690
I wouldn't have thought of that.

1003
01:19:17,299 --> 01:19:19,415
-All right, are you ready?
-Ready for what?

1004
01:19:19,499 --> 01:19:20,534
For this.

1005
01:19:21,259 --> 01:19:23,648
There's a window, Jack!
There's a window!

1006
01:19:26,059 --> 01:19:28,527
Is that your gun
or are you gettin' excited, man?

1007
01:19:28,619 --> 01:19:30,098
Get off me. Get off.

1008
01:19:31,219 --> 01:19:33,779
Police business. We're right on
out of here.

1009
01:19:36,419 --> 01:19:40,094
-Can you make it down to the lobby?
-Yeah, I'll be all right.

1010
01:19:41,099 --> 01:19:42,896
The elevator was broken.

1011
01:20:20,619 --> 01:20:23,292
Has anybody ever told you
you're a real pain in the ass?

1012
01:20:23,379 --> 01:20:24,573
All the time.

1013
01:20:28,139 --> 01:20:30,573
You're not gonna have to hear it anymore.

1014
01:20:31,899 --> 01:20:35,209
I'm gonna take care of you
like I took care of your ex-wife.

1015
01:21:00,499 --> 01:21:01,852
Here we are.

1016
01:21:03,579 --> 01:21:06,298
When you wake up in the morning
and look in the mirror...

1017
01:21:06,379 --> 01:21:08,688
...l think you're probably happy...

1018
01:21:08,859 --> 01:21:12,010
...pleased at what you see.
And that disturbs me.

1019
01:21:13,659 --> 01:21:16,219
So, I'm gonna take it on
as my responsibility...

1020
01:21:16,299 --> 01:21:19,735
...to make sure that you never get to look
in the mirror again.

1021
01:21:19,899 --> 01:21:23,687
I woke up happy, I'm going to bed happy
'cause you're gonna be dead.

1022
01:22:05,059 --> 01:22:06,538
Take your best shot.

1023
